<
py.Model.setOption
<! type method
<! sortname optionS
<! brief
<Set a new value for an option.
<! arg name: str
<The option name.
<! arg value: Union[int, float]
<The new option value.
<
<
<! note
<User may use `Options.XXX` to specify option name.
<
<
py.Model.write
<! type method
<! brief
<Write this model to a file. 
<! arg fname: str
<The output file name. The compression type is encoded in the file name as a suffix (.gz, .bz2), for instance "model.output.gz" implies a gzip compression type.
<! note
<A model with user defined function (aka. UDF) can not be serialized to file.
<
<
py.OptionConstClass
<! type class
<! brief
<A namespace to hold option names. It has a builtin instance `admm.Options`.
<
<For example:
<
<```python
<# Set the maximum number of iterations as 1000 for solving the original problem
<model.setOption(admm.Options.admm_max_iteration, 1000)
<```
