py.Param
<! type class
<! base TensorLike
<! brief
<Parameter is a place-holder for constant at modeling phase. Parameter has a shape but its data is undetermined at modeling phase.
<
<
py.Param.__init__
<! type method
<! brief
<Construct a new parameter.
<! arg name: str
<The name for new parameter.
<! arg *shape: int
<The parameter shape.
<! arg **attr: bool
<The attribute parameter has.
<Attributes include:
<  * nonneg
<  * nonpos
<  * symmetric
<  * diag
<  * PSD
<  * NSD
<  * pos
<  * neg
<! exmaple
<p = Param("p0", 2, 3, nonneg=True)
<
<
py.Param.attr
<! type int
<! brief
<The declared attribute for parameter.
<
<Attributes include:
<  * nonneg = 0
<  * nonpos = 1
<  * symmetric = 2
<  * diag = 3
<  * PSD = 4
<  * NSD = 5
<  * pos = 6
<  * neg = 7
<
<For example, if parameter is declared as PSD, this value is 16(1 << 4).
<
<
py.Param.name
<! type str
<! brief
<The name of this parameter
<
